Usage: assignTSV [-help] [-write_down_level_bump] [ -selected <netName> | [[-signal | -pgpad ] [-feedthru | -nonFeedthru ] [-net <netList> | -exclude_net <excludeNetList>] [-area <llx lly urx ury ...>] [-exclude_region <llx lly urx ury ...>] [-tsvViaName <string>] [-interposer ] ] ] [{[-backBump ] [-frontBump ]} [-force_current_die ]]

-help                                     # Prints out the command usage
-area <llx lly urx ury ...>               # assign bump or tsv in the specified
                                          # area (double, optional)
-backBump                                 # Assign back bumps (bool, optional)
-exclude_net <excludeNetList>             # specified net not to assign
                                          # (string, optional)
-exclude_region <llx lly urx ury ...>     # assign bump or tsv out of the
                                          # specified area (double, optional)
-feedthru                                 # Assign feedthru nets
                                          # (bool, optional)
-force_current_die                        # assign all io pins to backside
                                          # bumps or frontside bump directly
                                          # without checking xml file and top
                                          # level netlist. (bool, optional)
-frontBump                                # Assign front bumps (bool, optional)
-interposer                               # No instance on chip
                                          # (bool, optional)
-net <netList>                            # specified net to assign
                                          # (string, optional)
-nonFeedthru                              # Assign nonFeedthru nets
                                          # (bool, optional)
-pgpad                                    # Assign Power/Ground
                                          # (bool, optional)
-selected <netName>                       # Assign selected TSVs and Bumps to
                                          # specified net (string, optional)
-signal                                   # Assign signals (bool, optional)
-tsvViaName <string>                      # Assign TSV with specified master
                                          # name (string, optional)
-write_down_level_bump                    # write down level bump file for each
                                          # hinstance. (bool, optional)